<tr>
<td colspan=3 class=black><br><p><font class=b>How to play</font><br><font class=black>
- Each of seven Columns is dealt seven cards. In the first four Columns, the first three cards are deal face down - The Scorpion's tail. All other cards are dealt face up. Three cards will remain in the Stock.<br>
- Columns are built Down in the Same Suit. For example, a 6 of clubs may only be placed onto a 7 of clubs.<br>
- Any number of face up cards may be moved whether in sequence or not provided the above build rule is applied.<br>
- When a face down card is the topmost card in a Column, it is flipped face up.<br>
- Empty Columns may be filled with Kings.<br>
- One point is scored for each card built within a Column starting with a King. For example, if a Column has a K, Q, and J of the same suit in sequence then three points are scored for that combination.<br>
- Three cards will remain in the Stock after the deal. When play comes to a standstill (or sooner if desired,) clicking on the stock deals it's three cards one each to the first three Columns.<br>






























































































































